<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource  
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource">
A <b>Required_resource</b> is a  representation of resources needed in order to achieve a specified objective. The role of a required resource is determined by classification.
<example number="1">
 "facility", "test equipment", "supervisor" are examples of classifications of a required resource.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource.name">
the text by which the required resource is known.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource.description">
the text that further characterizes the required resource. The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource  Attribute: required_quantity 
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource.required_quantity"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource.required_quantity">
the required quantity of the required resource. 
<example number="2">Quantity can be specified using amount or duration.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_assignment">
A <b>Required_resource_assignment</b> is an association of a resource requirement statement with one or
more entities that requires the resource. 
<example number="1">task, task step, activity, activity method, organization are examples of entities to which the resource requirement statement could be related.</example>
The role of the assignment is determined by classification.
<example number="2">
The assignment can be classified as "required by".
</example>
<note>
An association between a required resource and actions that are needed
prior to its usage. </note>
<example number="3">A resource required by the activity "12" needs to be calibrated prior to usage. 
The calibration activity "21" is associated with the same required resource.using</example>
<example number="4">A resource required by the task "123" needs to be disposed after its usage. 
This disposal task "456" is associated with the same required resource.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_assignment  Attribute: assigned_resource 
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_assignment.assigned_resource"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_assignment.assigned_resource">
the required resource that is to be associated with the requiring entity.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_assignment  Attribute: item
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_assignment.item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_assignment.item">
the entity to which the required resource statement is assigned.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_by_resource_item  
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_resource_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_resource_item">
A <b>Required_resource_by_resource_item</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource"/>

 that is a statement of a required resource that can be identified within the application context.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_by_resource_item  Attribute: resource_item 
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_resource_item.resource_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_resource_item.resource_item">
a reference to an item that is defined as a resource within the application context. 
It can refer to an actual as well as to a type of resource.
<example>
Tool kit, facility, and  product category are examples of resource items.
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_by_specification  
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_specification"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_specification">
A <b>Required_resource_by_specification</b> is a  type of <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource"/>

 that is a statement of a required resource that is specified. A required resource that is specified may have multiple
different realizations. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship">
A <b>Required_resource_relationship</b> is a relationship between two required resource statements. The meaning of the relationship is determined by classification.
<example number="1">
"alternative" and "realized by" are examples of required resource relationship.
</example>
<example number="2">
A <express_ref
linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_specification"/>
for a power supply can be realized by a <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_resource_item"/>

 with part
number "ABC-1234".
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_relationship  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship.name">
the text by which the relationship is known.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_relationship  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship.description">
the text that further characterizes the relationship. The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_relationship  Attribute: relating 
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship.relating"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship.relating">
one of the instances of <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource"/> that is a part of  the relationship.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_relationship  Attribute: related 
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship.related"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship.related">
the other instance of  <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource"/> that is a  part of  the relationship. If one element of  the relationship is dependent upon the other, this attribute shall be the dependent one.
</ext_description>
